5 Mapping

The genome annotation is indexed with STAR –runMode genomeGenerate. Then the merged file of the chimeric reads is aligned to the genome annotation with STAR –runMode alignReads. For STAR settings see configurations. Obtained bam files are indexed with samtools index.

5.1 Obtaining crosslinks

The deduplicated bam files are then converted into bed files with bedtools bamtobed. The reads are shifted 1nt upstream (5’ direction) with bedtools shift -m 1 -p -1 because the UV-crosslink should be positioned 1nt before. To allow visualization in a genome browser the 1nt crosslink bed file is then also converted to .bigWig file using bedGraphToBigWig. Furthermore these bigWig files are merged with bigWigMerge by the experiment groups, specified by the user.
